{"word":"H2921 - טָלָא - ṭâlâʼ - taw-law' - Clouted","slug":"H2921","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">טָלָא</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ṭâlâʼ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>taw-law'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Clouted"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D8;&#x05DC;&#x05D0; - t&#x0323;a&#x0302;la&#x0302;'</b> - <i>taw-law'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>cover</i> with pieces; that is, (by implication) to <i>spot</i> or <i>variegate</i> (as tapestry): - clouted, with divers colours, spotted."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2923\">H2923</a>"}]}